ReviewText: This is my favourite blend from Nescafé.Its dark strong & tastes so good ,like real coffee should.I buy this coffee everywhere we travel & one thing you can be sure of the quality is always excellent
Title: For that perfect cup of coffee

ClientResponses.Response: It's really sad to hear you're not a fan of the new recipe. During the recent recipe change, micro ground coffee was added to NESCAFÉ Gold Blend. This is non-soluble coffee and gives you a similar experience to that of a barista made coffee! It can also leave a residue at the bottom of your cup. We've made a note of your feedback & will be passing it on to the rest of the team.

ReviewText: I always chose Nescafe Gold Black as it was strong and flavoursome and almost as good as a proper filter coffee. I noticed the new jar but just thought it was a rebranding exercise and bought it as usual. I could not have been more wrong-the whole taste of the coffee has changed-it is really bitter and has a horrid and unpalatable aftertaste. Worse still it does not dissolve properly whatever I do to try to encourage it to do so and leaves a vile gloopy black sludge in the bottom of my mug. I will not be buying this product again
Title: So disappointing and so not worth the bother

ReviewText:
I usually buy Gold Blend but on seeing the new Gold Blend BLACK I decided to buy a jar of this on Friday and immediately opened it to make a cuppa. On opening the coffee aroma was so inviting and smelt just like freshly ground coffee.
I chose to drink it black and it was rich and strong but oh so smooth and not a trace of bitterness. It will be permanently on my shopping list from now on.
Title: BLACK from Nescafe is fantastic, smooth and rich.

Photos.Caption: The Legend that is Elvis with the Legend That is Nescafe

ReviewText: I first tried Nescafe Gold Black a few months back, now I am hooked and nothing comes close to the smooth unique taste that enlightens my mouth, getting up in the mornings used to be a chore now I cant wait to get up from my slumber to enjoy the taste that is Nescafe Gold Black. I wouldn't hesitate to recommend this coffee to caffeine lovers around the world !!
Title: Nescafe Gold a taste to behold !

ReviewText:
If you long for a journey that takes you beyond the depths of the darkest chocolate then this is the coffee for you. Instantly the aroma reaches the senses, you can taste the smell before it touches your lips. A cup of Nescafe Gold Black is like laying on a feather pillow after banging your head against the wall of coffees as you strive to find instant satisfaction within a jar.

Serving suggestion - Indulge yourself in a decedent after dinner treat. Simply make a cup of Nescafe Gold Black and pour over a good quality vanilla ice cream, dust with cinnamon or cocoa powder  - heaven
Title: As dark as midnight chocolate

ReviewText: Delicate, beautifully made. Can’t start my day without nescafe. The first drink i have every morning and last drink i have before go to ber. I literally can’t live without my coffee..THANKS NESCAFE☕️
Title: Loving this coffee

ClientResponses.Response: Thanks for getting in touch & letting us know your thoughts on the changes we've made. Each of the jars still have a coloured label on the front to ensure consumers can still find them in store. We really value your feedback & will be letting the rest of the team know!

ReviewText:
Firstly, this product is now hard to differentiate between the other "Gold" varieties on the shelf - they all look the same. It took me ages to find it having first thought that Black Gold had been discontinued.
Secondly, Nestle, what possessed you to add ground coffee??? If I wanted ground coffee in my instant I would buy Azera (or similar), which I don't because I don't like it. Although I appreciate that it is very finely ground, it still gives a grainy texture to the coffee - which I noticed immediately in my first cup from the new jar. It also unbalances what was a really good smooth & rich tasting coffee making it bitter, grainy and, well, not very rounded.  Overall Nestle very poor. Having been a Black Gold drinker for almost 8 years now, I will no longer be buying this.
Title: "If it ain't broke don't fix it"

ReviewText: There is only one thing, well two.., that I'm looking forward in the morning.... my Nescafe intense and my scramble egg... while I eat my eggs my gold coffee will rest till reach the right temperature (for me at least!) and then it's mine !!! waking me up slowly but surely... ahhh thanks buddy !!! \m/
Title: the new GOLD is BLACK

ReviewText: I've been through the range of Nescafe products, from the standard Gold Blend (My usual Tipple) and Nescafe Original (Not good in my opinion), to some of the fancier ranges like Nescafe Asta La Vista (or whatever it's called) ... I've always gone back to standard Gold Blend, now having tried the Black version I'm converted ... I always drink strong coffee anyway (3 or 4 tea spoons) so it's a welcome relief to have a stronger blend.  It has a good, hearty "feet up in the winter in front of a roaring fire" vibe to it, with smokey rich flavours.  It's a great everyday cup of coffee
Title: Strong, Hearty coffee

ClientResponses.Response: Thanks for getting in touch & letting us know! It's sad to hear you're not liking the changes but we appreciate your feedback.

ClientResponses.Response: We're really disappointed to hear this. If you don’t like the rich taste, or the micro ground coffee, you could try NESCAFÉ Crema, which has taste similar to NESCAFÉ Gold Blend, however is smoother, and does not contain micro ground coffee.

ReviewText: I'm so sad that you have chosen to ruin my favourite drink. It now closely resembles a cheap supermarket brand coffee. If I wanted a "Barista style" coffee with sludge at the bottom I wouldn't be drinking Gold Blend in the first place. (Perhaps you could bring out "Gold Blend Original"???
Title: You spoiled my favourite coffee

ClientResponses.Response: Hey Hilary, thank you for getting in touch with us. We've added micro ground coffee to our NESCAFÉ Gold Blend to give it a richer aroma whilst maintaining the same smoothness. It's a shame you don't enjoy the changes. We'll be making a note of your comments.

ReviewText: Bought this 2weeks ago and my husband says it is tasteless needs a very heaped spoon to get any taste he normally drinks Original Nescafe or Alta Rica.  I find it watery and a little bitter and normally drink Nescafe Gold, Colombian or Alta Rica.  Very disappointed won't by again
Title: What taste?

ReviewText: I am upset that the recipe has changed, it tastes now like the low-range supermarket own-brand coffees. It seems the granules are different, with a stiffer mouthfeel. The roasted beans add to it a bit of a burnt taste

ReviewText: have been using this coffee for years, probably since shortly after it came out.   Before this we drank Nescafe Gold but the Black has got so much more taste without being bitter.
Title: strong but wonderful taste.

ReviewText: I was on a quest for an instant coffee that could be passed  off as percolated  but without the hassle. An easy task? Oh no - it's a jungle out there - the seemingly 'obvious' ones were unpleasantly  bitter  - I'm still looking for ways of using them up. But I knew there was one for me (and my unsuspecting visitors) out there somewhere - determination paid off and Nescafe Gold Black  gets a 5* from me and satisfied guests.
Title: Impress the guests

ReviewText: buy this coffee all the time,enjoy my coffee strong,this blend really tickles the taste buds,and unlike normal coffee i have to have two teaspoons for a decent cup, with gold blend dark i just need one,have trouble finding it stores seem to stock it then stop and start so I usually stock up when I find it,good job I live on my own would begrufed sharing it,sorry for the spelling
Title: BOLD

ReviewText: Why have you changed my coffee of choice when you changed the jar, I am 65 years old and have used Nescafe coffee all my life, I drink black coffee and switched to the black gold when it came out so quite some years ago and have always been happy with it until now, I still had several of the old jars when the new one came out wish I had more The coffee in the new jars leave a horrible powder at the bottom of you cup or mug. It seems to be a cheaper product. Not happy and will be changing my coffee. Before you changed the coffee I would have given it 5 now I would give it 0 if I could. I am not a tea drinker and drink coffee black without sugar so the flavour of the coffee is important please bring back the old black gold as it used to be before the jar change
Title: Black gold

ReviewText: I have drunk original Gold Blend for more years than I care to remember. Of late I found the taste has changed and become very weak and lack lustre. Gold Blend Black is a vast improvement. I use a coffee machine  regularly but find Gold Black for an instant coffee is almost as good in flavour. Rich and strong like coffee should be! It's  a winner for me
Title: Full bodied

ReviewText: nescafe gold is a rich strong flavour,ideal to wake up with and of an evening with a brandy or benedictine or whatever your tipple is,serve black with a measure of spirit,2 teaspoons sugar. and a layer of cream on top,pour cream over the back of a teaspoon to stop it sinking,with a dark choclate on the side:-)I find this coffee goes a long way due to the strength,its a touch of luxury and visitors will think is fresh coffee if you hide the jar and boil up a tiny amount in water to pervade the air before they come :-)
Title: strikingly strong

ReviewText: I'm a massive coffee snob, for my sins, I really don't like instant coffee and unfortunately we have no decent coffee maker at work, but when I tried Nescafe GOLD Black I was amazed at the taste of the blend. The taste wasn't the usually 'irony' taste I get off instant coffee, it was a rich and deep roasted taste
Title: Fusspot

ReviewText: I was on holiday in the west of Ireland for a few weeks and with the weather changing so often it was nice to have the tasty, perfect and dependable Nestle Gold Blend coffee every morning, there is nothing like watching the sun rise in Ireland with the best cup of instant coffee in your hand.
Title: just so dependable and consistently good

ReviewText: I have been drinking Nescafe Gold Black for some years now and loved it. Recently the product changed, I think. The packaging certainly has and I now find that it is not as good. There is normally some powdery residue left in the cup and if you do not 'swill' the coffee around as the level drops, the residue can be quite a bit. It is still a nice cup of coffee, but not, in my opinion, as nice as it was prior to the recent change.
Title: Black Has Changed

Title: awful

ReviewText: I thought I'd try Nescafe Gold Black, from pouring on the hot water the fullness of the aroma filled the kitchen,so much so my wife joined me in a cup after catching the aroma!!  Could not wait to try this new blend from a quality name, so I took a sip on the way to my favourite chair, upon doing so I was instantly reminded and transported to a barista in Italy - its flavour overwhelmes your environment capivating you until the last drop - it's sheer endulgance that your worth.
Title: Ultimate luxury

ReviewText: I bought this a a few months ago it so nice the coffee great for when you need that extra kick
Title: Great taste

ReviewText: Normally when buying a instant dark coffee i find them to be way too bitter and taste quite dry, where as when i bought Nescafe Gold Black, it was so rich,dark and warming and i got no bitter aftertaste. For the price of about £8 it is definitely worth it. You get a great amount for the price and it lasts you quite a while. One thing i will say about it is, if you want it at its best, then make sure you have it hot... Like most coffees it doesn't taste as good cold.
Title: Great taste, Very Warming

ReviewText: I always keep a jar of Black Gold Coffee for after dinner with friends, when we want to enjoy a dark rich black coffee.  A couple of years ago, I bought an popular coffee machine.  After using it a couple of times, some friends - who had been for a dinner party said, "don't mean to be rude, but have you changed your coffee? - this isn't as good as the one we're used to here", gave the machine to Charity Shop & back to Black Gold, think that said it all.
Title: our "Grown-up After Dinner Coffee"

ReviewText: I normally drink freshly ground and brewed coffee but have been very busy lately and have been foregoing my coffee when I just haven't had the time for making my usual brew. However, fed up of my caffeine withdrawals, my sister introduced me to Nescafé Gold Black and my life has been revolutionized! I can now have a lovely rich dark coffee in a fraction of the time and am a much better person with my caffeine hit in the mornings :-) Thank you Nescafé
Title: Great coffee

ReviewText:
Recently tried this coffee as I’m a coffee lover and have many Nescafé products yet find this definitely to the connoisseur in me, a defined cup of Gold.
Using a frothy milk to give this a twist is ideal.
2 sugars and it’s done.
The process of turning the kettle on and preparing each part of making this is enjoyable and worth the effort.
The many different styles of this Gold should accommodate the various Gold Rush drinkers in us all.
Title: Strong coffee to get you going in the morning.

ReviewText:
I have always enjoyed this dark blend of coffee, very full flavoured , wonderful aroma and great anytime of day. The jar contains over 100 servings and the last is as good as the first! The quality of the coffee is not diminished once opened. I take a jar to work and virtually all my colleagues will ask for a spoonful! Just as well it does hold so many servings!! 
I wholeheartedly recommend this coffee to any coffee lovers!
Title: Perfect Everytime!

ReviewText: NESCAFE Gold Black its rich, intense, aroma awakens my senses every morning...mmmm, followed by the taste of GOLD upon my tongue, rich, dark, smooth, waking my mind, body and spirits EVERY morning!  Nescafe Gold Black rich, beautiful, coffee without any bitterness that many other 'intense' coffees can suffer from.  A GOLD standard coffee that is decadent but affordable enough to drink all day every day!
Title: Black is MY new GOLD!

ReviewText: I have been buying this coffee for years! No other coffee comes anywhere close to this. Now it's changed and at first I was upset, it is a finer blend and leaves some deposit in the end... But the strength I always crave is still there...  The richness that fulfils me is still there... The great taste is always there. It's just  a little more sophisticated...  I can live with that!
Title: Delightful full body of sophistication!

ReviewText:
Bought this for a change when it first came out. I found it had a nice coffee smell when i opened the jar. When hot water is poured on the granules ot has a creamy appearance. Overall it is a more intense Gold blend flavour but without a delayed aftertaste that sometimes occurs after some coffees.
Definitely my favourite choice having been a gold blend drinker for over 35 years
Title: Stronger but velvety taste

ReviewText:
Usually buy expensive Colombian coffee but noticed new branding so thought i would give it a try. Take my coffee black , so always get a good idea on flavour .
Was really surprised by full bodied taste at a much more competitive price of the coffee I used to buy . Well done Nescafe...you coffee lovers out there, give Nescafe Gold Black a taste , you wont be dissappointed.
Title: Great taste...

ReviewText: Any coffee lover is going to prefer freshly ground roasted beans, slowly percolated to draw out a full flavour. Reality is though that we seldom have that much time on our hands during a busy day. Hence the creation of Instant Coffee. With NEscafe Gold Black - you get the utter convenience of an instant but a flavour which gets pretty darn close to a "proper" coffee taste.
Title: Instant enjoyment

ReviewText: As a very busy and in demand person I need a coffee in the morning which will give me the pick up and fly start to my day, Nescafe Gold Black is my number one drink with its rich and full bodied strong taste it gives me the kick start that I need to power my adrenaline to cope with whatever the day ahead will bring, as well as keeping me mentally and physically alert.
Title: My go to coffee in the morning

ReviewText: I have drunk Nescafe Gold for years and recently picked up another jar, or so I thought, to find it was Gold Black, when I got home. The first mug was enough to bless my mistake, the flavour is excellent and really enjoyable. I have taken Cappuchino sachets to work as I don't like the brand they provide but when my stock is finished I think it will be Gold Black.
Title: Sharp Beautiful Taste

ReviewText: I thought I'd give this a try, a change from my regular brand which would be hard to beat. This was absolutely delicious! A strong, but not bitter, a toasted coffee bean on the nose also got a hint of black treacle, vanilla aroma. This was exceptionally smooth, no bitter after taste that you associate with strong coffees. Delicious !! I have to buy this again!
Title: Exceptionally Smooth

ReviewText: I have always been a fan of Nescafe but when I discovered this range I fell in love with it. It is as strong as it is necessary to wake me up in the morning and not many can take credit for that! Full of flavour and distinctive taste. I have also used it in cakes and find that is perfect for them to get a lovely coffee aroma.  I would recommend to everyone.
Title: Excellent flavour

ReviewText:
As coffee lovers we thought we'd try something different to our usual brand and decided to try Nescafe Gold Black.

To say we were impressed is an understatement!

The Nescafe Gold Black, is rich, smooth and aromatic.  It smells so good that you just can't resist.

The taste is delightful, leaving you wanting more and more!

Simply divine!
Title: Simply the best!

ReviewText: I bought this about 3 weeks ago to try , as I'd heard good things from my friends , I usually drink Nescafe Original and never dreamed that after so many years of drinking the same wonderful coffee that I would be transformed into a totally NEW experience . It is a wonderful flavour and I can see myself drinking this coffe for years to come !!!
Title: Transformed

ReviewText: I am a huge fan of black Americano coffee and love to experiment with different beans. However sometimes when I am at home I need a fix of dark, smooth coffee in an instant. This new products really hits the spot for me, its dark and tasty without the bitterness when I heap up the spoon ! Thank you Nescafe for bringing the 'real' into coffee!!
Title: Hits the Americano spot !!

ReviewText: I have been a fan of Nescafe Gold Blend for years, so was intrigued to see this new addition. It couldn't possibly be as good, I thought. Wrong! It is in fact even better. It has all the richness, depth and aroma of the original Gold Blend, but with added body and flavour. It really is most delicious! I will most definitely keep buying it.
Title: Gorgeous coffee!

ReviewText: Recently changed from Gold Blend to the Black version, like my coffee with a strong full flavour whilst being smooth and not bitter as some of the coffee shop ones are, Black delivered in full, lovely full smooth flavour. Nice aroma when you open the jar for the first time, great value for money . My coffee of choice now as love the taste
Title: Lovely Flavour

ReviewText: I bought Nescafé Gold Black as my husband was complaining that all the coffees we’ve had recently are very tasteless and this one looked like a good strong option. As it turned out, I made a great choice as Gold Black has a lovely ‘proper’ coffee taste that my husband loves, as do I. It is now our go-to coffee that we enjoy every day.
Title: A ‘Proper’ Coffee Taste!

ReviewText: We have been drinking Alta Rica for as long as I can remember as it has that strong taste but none of the bitterness you get from cheaper roasts. Gave this a try and although it is better than the cheaper coffees it still hasn't the finesse that Alta Rica has. We have converted most of our friends to Alta Rica.
Title: Not bad but not as good as Alta Rica

ReviewText: This Nescafé is so rich and full-flavoured, yet not overpowering.  I really appreciate the first coffee and this coffee's a brilliant way to start any day.  However, Nescafé Gold Black's full body is also especially good made with hot milk, and is very satisfying with supper.  Great all round, I'm a big fan!
Title: Rich, great coffee!

ReviewText: I always drank carte noir, but one day I decided to try nescafe gold black, and for me nescafe has a smooth flavour and still you get that boost of caffeine, the different flavours is exceptional and I love drinking the decaff as well, it's so affordable and delicious to drink, would highly recommend it
Title: Coffee

I like really strong coffee and I usually use 3 teaspoons per cup, but with this I don't need to, it's really rich and smooth and intensely flavoured. The days I can't get to Starbucks I drink this and its fast taking over!
Title: Super smooth and intense

I always love tasting new coffee's and when I tried this, I was really happy as the flavour was just right full of body yet not bitter, this is now my new coffee, so well done Nescaf'e.
Great cooffee I would recommend this coffee to anyone that loves a full rounded coffee you won't be dissapointed.
Title: My New Coffee

Title: Better than usual instant coffee

Title: The best got better

ReviewText: I tried this on an introductory offer a few weeks ago and am hooked.  All the flavour of freshly brewed coffee with the convenience of instant.  I have since re-stocked and visitors think I have poured this from a caffetiere.  Good result all round.  Love the styish look of the packaging too.
Title: Exceptional!

ReviewText: Drunk Gold Blend since my childhood and recently switched to Gold Blend Black, as it was on offer and it was a wise decision. A much more intense coffee taste without the bitterness you can sometimes get or having to ask for an extra shot. If you like strong coffee, then i'd try this one out
Title: A change for the better

ReviewText: The roast characteristics of this coffee really stand out to me. The darker roast develops a more toffee like sweetness and a rich cocoa flavour is rounded off by the creamy mouthfeel, reminding me of chocolate. The acidity is very mild and there is a pleasant bitterness in the aftertaste.”
Title: The pleasure of chocolate.

ReviewText: I am still waiting for someone to bring out an instance coffee that tastes as good and strong as a percolated coffee.  I love a good tasting strong flavour to let me know I am drinking coffee and have still yet to find the exact replica.  Enjoyable however, just missing a little something.
Title: GOOD BUT NOT EXCELLENT!

ReviewText: Well you want a review, What can I say it is a lovely coffee if you like strong coffee this is the one for you. I only drink strong black coffee and to be honest this is the only one that I drink. If you like ground coffee this is the one for you all the flavour without the mess.
Title: Ground coffee without the mess

ReviewText: I bought this on offer instead of my usual Nescafe aand am so happy that I went straight out and bought 6 more jars.  The flavour is rich and smooth and its how coffee should taste the value for money is excellent, it is like having a barista grind it fresh and make it for you.
Title: Gold is the new Black

Title: Nice strong coffee!

ReviewText: I first tried this brand about 3 months ago more by accident than design - I actually picked up the wrong jar when shopping.  So glad I did though.  This has one of the best tastes of an instant coffee I've ever tried.  It may have been a mistake the first time, but not since
Title: Perfect taste to wake up with

Title: GOLD Black

Title: Lovely, rich and just what I need first thing!

ReviewText: My normal coffee was out of stock and I'm so glad it was!! Never have I tasted an instant coffee with so much flavour, so much depth - and such an enticing aroma! Once I started drinking it in the office, the jar didn't last long - now it is our coffee of choice.
Title: This can't be instant coffee!!

ReviewText: The taste, the smell, the feeling from this coffee leaves me feeling, satisfied and ready to combat the day ahead of me. I feel like I'm treating myself to something indulgent with every cup. I have been converted to a nescafe coffee snob, in the best kind of way
Title: Fell in love with coffee again

Title: Smells like freshly roasted coffee beans

Title: like my men Strong.

ReviewText: Love gold blend , I like a quite strong coffee this fits the bill,   has a fuller flavour, no aftertaste and really has the taste of a premium coffee.Tastes perfect either black or with milk. When you want a cup of coffee this is the one i would recommend.
Title: Excellent taste

Title: Totally Refreshing

ReviewText: Nescafe gold Black is a rich cup of coffee, so easily enjoyed on its own or with your favourite biscuit. I love the aroma when you twist the lid and open the jar. My favourite mug of the day is with breakfast, the smell, the taste the warmth, oh so good.
Title: Very enjoyable cup of coffee

ReviewText: I bought this instead of my usual variety and found that it is much better than that!  It makes delicious black coffee but a friend says that it was also great with milk. Strong but a good taste. No bitterness or aftertaste. I am definitely converted
Title: Makes excellent black coffee
